<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; bEditID:r3st1; color:#000000; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" size="2" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;"><br></span></font></div><div style="text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation} {!Contact.LastName},</span></font></div><div style=""><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"></font></span></div><span lang="en-GB" style="text-align: start; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><div style="margin: 0px;"><br></div><div style="margin: 0px;"><p dir="ltr" style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">As promised we have now completed a review of the Rewards and Behaviour Policy for BSY Secondary School. As you know this was a single document addressing rewards and behaviour. Please click on link below:</span></p><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><p dir="ltr" style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1w8n8lRhV9vm0jP3X96qDV5nyaNGvlisxAfLwcp5CCHM/edit?ts=5c6d2027">Secondary Rewards and Behaviour Policy January 2019</a></span></p><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><p dir="ltr" style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">This revised policy reflects the desire to create a positive environment and celebrating the many successes of our students in as many different ways as possible. To this end we have also considered and included new ways of thanking, appreciating and rewarding students for all the great things they do in our school. Secondary students often ask for more tangible rewards and we will continue to work with students and keep this under review so that we get the balance right.</span></p><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><p dir="ltr" style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: justify;"><span style="background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">As part of this review the secondary student council and secondary students were also asked to input into what they wanted to see in their place of study in the form of a student charter. This important piece of work will also help to inform the current ongoing work on missions and values for the school alongside the golden rules and rewards system that Primary already have in place.</span></p><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><p dir="ltr" style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: justify;"><span style="background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">As we all know, students are generally very well behaved in our school. Nevertheless, as you would expect we have very high standards for all our students and they have have high expectations of themselves. Occasionally, there is a need to address behaviours or patterns of behaviour that fall short of our expectations and that of the agreed student charter. We have set out a short, simple and clear section on behaviour and support both within and beyond the classroom. </span></p><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><p dir="ltr" style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: justify;"><span style="background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">As I know, you will all appreciate that as the school grows we have to strike a good balance for the school and for the whole community. Parents and students clearly have differing views and beliefs on how the school might approach this subject.</span></p><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><p dir="ltr" style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: justify;"><span style="background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Teachers and students today, have all been updated on this review and we will be looking to ensure a fairness and consistency in approach to this policy. </span></p><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><p dir="ltr" style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: justify;"><span style="background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">There will be a further review of the policy in July once the work on the school missions and values is complete. There will be no further review to this policy until then. </span></p><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><p dir="ltr" style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: justify;"><span style="background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Thank you for your continued support. </span></p><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><p dir="ltr" style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: justify;"><span style="background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Paul Holyome</span><span style="background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">	</span><span style="background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">	</span><span style="background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Matthew Gilberthorpe</span></p><div><br></div></div></font></span></div><div style="text-align: left;"><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font size="2" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="">The British School Yangon</font></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);" size="2">www.britishschoolyangon.org</font></p></div></div>]]></td>
